<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="http://archives.state.ut.us/eadarchives.xsl"?><ead xmlns="urn:isbn:1-931666-22-9" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xsi:schemaLocation="urn:isbn:1-931666-22-9 http://www.loc.gov/ead/ead.xsd"><eadheader langencoding="iso639-2b" scriptencoding="iso15924" relatedencoding="dc" repositoryencoding="iso15511" countryencoding="iso3166-1" dateencoding="iso8601"><eadid countrycode="US" mainagencycode="US-U-Ar" publicid="-//State of Utah::Utah State Archives and Records Service//TEXT (US::U-Ar::U-Ar_18193.xml::Civil registers of actions)//EN" encodinganalog="identifier">U-Ar_18193</eadid><filedesc><titlestmt><titleproper encodinganalog="title">Inventory of Civil registers of actions from District Court (Fifth District : Washington County), <date era="ce" calendar="gregorian" normal="1850/2013" encodinganalog="date" certainty="approximate">1896-1990.</date></titleproper><titleproper type="filing" altrender="nodisplay" encodinganalog="title">District Court (Fifth District : Washington County) Civil registers of actions</titleproper><author encodinganalog="creator">Utah State Archives and Records Service</author><sponsor encodinganalog="contributor">Library Services and Technology Act (LSTA) grant, 2007-2008</sponsor></titlestmt><publicationstmt><publisher encodinganalog="publisher">Utah State Archives and Records Service</publisher><address><addressline>346 SOUTH RIO GRANDE</addressline><addressline>SALT LAKE CITY, UT 84101-1106</addressline><addressline>801-533-3535</addressline><addressline>historyresearch@utah.gov</addressline></address><date era="ce" calendar="gregorian" normal="2013" encodinganalog="date">2013</date></publicationstmt></filedesc><profiledesc><creation>This series was processed by David Clark in 03/2000. Initial EAD encoding was completed by Elizabeth Perkes in <date era="ce" calendar="gregorian" normal="2000-08" encodinganalog="date">August 2000.</date>. Encoding system was created by Elizabeth Perkes in <date era="ce" calendar="gregorian" normal="2007-12" encodinganalog="date">December 2007.</date>.</creation><langusage>Finding aid written in <language encodinganalog="language" langcode="eng" scriptcode="Latn">English</language> in Latin script.</langusage><descrules>Finding aid based on DACS (<title render="italic">Describing Archives: A Content Standard</title>).</descrules></profiledesc><revisiondesc><change><date era="ce" calendar="gregorian" normal="20080923" encodinganalog="date">09/23/2008</date><item>Finding aid reviewed for DACS and Utah Manuscript Association's EAD Best Practice Guidelines by Gina Strack.</item></change><change><date era="ce" calendar="gregorian" normal="20110126" encodinganalog="date">01/26/2011</date><item>Standardized the container list.</item></change></revisiondesc></eadheader><archdesc level="series" type="inventory" relatedencoding="dc"><did><repository><corpname encodinganalog="publisher">Utah State Archives and Records Service </corpname><address><addressline>300 South Rio Grande</addressline><addressline>Salt Lake City, UT 84101-1182</addressline><addressline>801-533-3535</addressline><addressline>historyresearch@utah.gov</addressline></address></repository><unitid encodinganalog="identifier" countrycode="US" repositorycode="US-U-Ar">Series 18193</unitid><origination label="creator" encodinganalog="agency" id="ID_1682"><corpname rules="dacs" encodinganalog="creator" role="creator">District Court (Fifth District : Washington County)</corpname></origination><unittitle encodinganalog="title">District Court (Fifth District : Washington County) Civil registers of actions</unittitle><unitdate type="inclusive" era="ce" calendar="gregorian" normal="1850/2013" encodinganalog="date">1896-1990.</unitdate><physdesc><extent encodinganalog="format">12.00 cubic feet and 29 microfilm reels</extent></physdesc><abstract encodinganalog="description">The register of action for the Washington County Fifth District court contains entries pertaining to civil cases and assists with tracking documents filed for each case.</abstract><physloc encodinganalog="location">These records are housed in the Utah State Archives' permanent storage room.</physloc><langmaterial><language langcode="eng" encodinganalog="language">English</language></langmaterial></did><bioghist encodinganalog="description"><head>Historical Note</head><p>An <extref xlink:href="http://archives.utah.gov/research/agencyhistories/1682.html">agency history</extref> is available.</p></bioghist> <scopecontent encodinganalog="description"><p>Civil cases document the legal process and the administration of justice in conjunction with civil proceedings for the determination of a controversy between parties wherein rights are enforced or protected, or wrongs are prevented or redressed. Records and documents pertaining to a particular civil action are filed together by the court clerk and collectively these documents constitute the case file. As these records or actions are filed, the clerk enters them in the registers which comprise this series. The clerk is required as documents enter the case file to make a notation that shows "the nature of each paper filed or writ issued and the substance of each order or judgment of the court and of the returns showing execution of process. The notation of an order or judgment shall show the date the notation is made. When trial by jury has been properly demanded or ordered the clerk shall enter the word 'jury' on the page assigned to that action" [UCA 79 (b) (2)].</p><p> A register of actions may contain the following entries for each civil case: name of the attorney for plaintiff and defendant, name of the judge presiding over the case, petitions, complaints, summons, answers to summons, orders from the court, assignment of judges, exhibits, judgment, findings and conclusions, costs, decrees, requests by attorneys for instructions to the jury, verdict, motions for cross complaints or new trials, amendments to previous answers and disclaimers.</p></scopecontent><arrangement encodinganalog="description"><p>Numerical by case number, thereunder chronological</p></arrangement> <accessrestrict encodinganalog="rights"><p> This series is classified as Public.</p></accessrestrict><userestrict encodinganalog="rights"><p>These records are available for reproduction and use.</p></userestrict><prefercite><p> Cite the Utah State Archives and Records Service, the creating agency name, the series title, and the series number.</p> </prefercite><acqinfo><p>These records were acquired from the creating agency through established retention schedules.</p></acqinfo><processinfo><p> Registers of Actions were first scheduled in 1983 as permanent records. This series was archivally processed by David Clark in March 2000. A separate filming of the records took place in 2007 as part of a grant project designed to preserve the records of Utah's Fifth District Courts. Archival processing of new holdings was completed by Jim Kichas in July 2007.</p></processinfo><otherfindaid><p> Indexes: An alphabetical index is located at the beginning of each register.</p></otherfindaid><relatedmaterial encodinganalog="relation"><p>Civil case files from the District Court (Fifth District : Washington County), <extref xlink:href="http://archives.state.ut.us/cgi-bin/eadseriesget.cgi?WEBINPUT_BIBLGRPC_KEY=3635">Series 3635</extref>, contains the entire case file listed in these registers.</p><p>Register of actions from the District Court (Fifth District : Washington County), Series 23737, include civil cases as well.</p><p>Index to civil and criminal actions from the District Court (Fifth District : Washington County), <extref xlink:href="http://archives.state.ut.us/cgi-bin/eadseriesget.cgi?WEBINPUT_BIBLGRPC_KEY=26247">Series 26247</extref>, provide specific dates for actions in the cases cited in this index.</p></relatedmaterial><controlac